---
import LegalPage from '../../layouts/LegalPage.astro';
---

<LegalPage
  title="Privacy Policy"
  subtitle="KickWiz Privacy Policy — how we collect, use, and protect your data."
  lastUpdated="17 April 2026"
>
  <h2>1. Overview</h2>
  <p>
    KickWiz ("we", "our", "the App") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect,
    how we use it, and your rights regarding your information. This policy complies with the Apple App Store
    guidelines, the Australian Privacy Act 1988, and applicable data protection regulations.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>

  <h3>2.1 Data You Provide</h3>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Data Type</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Linked to Identity</th><th>Used for Tracking</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Name</strong> (via Sign in with Apple)</td><td>Display personalisation</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>User ID</strong> (local device UUID)</td><td>App functionality</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sign in with Apple</strong>: If you choose to sign in, we receive your name and an anonymised Apple user identifier. Apple may provide a private relay email address. We store this locally on your device only.</li>
    <li><strong>API Key</strong> (optional): Pro users may provide their own Anthropic API key, stored securely in the iOS Keychain.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Data We Collect Automatically</h3>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Data Type</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Storage</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Subscription status</strong></td><td>Unlock Pro features</td><td>Apple-managed (StoreKit)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Cached match data</strong></td><td>Offline access, performance</td><td>Device-only (SwiftData)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Generated predictions</strong></td><td>Analysis display</td><td>Device + backend (anonymised)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3>2.3 Data We Do NOT Collect</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Location data</li>
    <li>Contacts or address book</li>
    <li>Photos or media</li>
    <li>Browsing history</li>
    <li>Advertising identifiers (IDFA)</li>
    <li>Device fingerprints</li>
    <li>Health or fitness data</li>
    <li>Financial or payment information (handled entirely by Apple)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>App Functionality</strong>: Display your name, manage subscription tier, generate predictions, cache data for offline use.</li>
    <li><strong>AI Analysis</strong> (Pro tier): When you request AI-powered analysis, match statistics (team names, scores, player stats, injury data) are sent to Anthropic's Claude API for processing. <strong>No personal information is included in AI requests.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Prediction Storage</strong>: Generated predictions are sent anonymously to our backend for post-match accuracy tracking. No user identifier is attached.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. AI Processing Disclosure</h2>

  <h3>4.1 What AI Processes</h3>
  <p>KickWiz uses Anthropic's Claude AI to enhance match predictions for Pro subscribers. The AI processes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Team statistics and form data</li>
    <li>Player performance metrics</li>
    <li>Historical match results</li>
    <li>Venue and conditions data</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2 What AI Does NOT Process</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Your name or identity</li>
    <li>Your location</li>
    <li>Your betting history or financial data</li>
    <li>Any personal information</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.3 AI Data Handling</h3>
  <p>
    Data sent to Anthropic's API is processed under Anthropic's Usage Policy. Anthropic does not use API inputs
    to train models. AI-generated content is clearly labelled within the App as "Deep AI Analysis."
  </p>

  <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>Data Shared</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Apple (StoreKit)</strong></td><td>Subscription transactions</td><td>Payment processing</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Anthropic Claude API</strong></td><td>Match statistics (no PII)</td><td>AI analysis (Pro only)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Squiggle API</strong></td><td>None (read-only)</td><td>AFL match data source</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>KickWiz Backend</strong></td><td>Anonymous predictions</td><td>Accuracy tracking</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for marketing or advertising purposes.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>On-device</strong>: User preferences stored in UserDefaults; API keys in iOS Keychain (encrypted at rest); cached data in SwiftData (encrypted on iOS 17+).</li>
    <li><strong>Backend</strong>: Anonymous prediction data stored on servers in Sydney, Australia (Fly.io). No user-identifiable information is stored server-side.</li>
    <li><strong>Encryption</strong>: All network communication uses HTTPS/TLS. Keychain data is protected by iOS hardware encryption.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>On-device data</strong>: Retained until you delete the App or clear data manually.</li>
    <li><strong>Backend predictions</strong>: Retained for the current AFL season for accuracy analysis; deleted after season end.</li>
    <li><strong>Apple Sign-In data</strong>: Stored locally only; deleted when you sign out or delete the App.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access</strong> your data: View all stored data within the App's Account section.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete</strong> your data: Delete the App to remove all local data. Contact us to request deletion of backend prediction data.</li>
    <li><strong>Opt out</strong> of AI processing: Use the free tier (no AI data sent to Anthropic).</li>
    <li><strong>Manage subscriptions</strong>: Cancel anytime via Settings &gt; Apple ID &gt; Subscriptions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    KickWiz is rated 17+ and is not intended for children under 17. We do not knowingly collect data from children.
    If you believe a child has provided us with data, contact us for removal.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. The "Last Updated"
    date at the top indicates the latest revision. Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Apple Privacy Manifest</h2>
  <p>This App includes a Privacy Manifest (PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy) declaring:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tracking</strong>: No tracking of users across apps or websites</li>
    <li><strong>Collected Data</strong>: User ID (device-local), Name (optional), Purchase History (subscription status)</li>
    <li><strong>Required Reason APIs</strong>: UserDefaults (CA92.1 — app functionality)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy inquiries or data deletion requests:<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@kickwiz.com">privacy@kickwiz.com</a>
  </p>
</LegalPage>
